<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-04-02T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-04-02T14:00:00-05:00" n="466" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d466">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">865.85/274: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-02T21:00:00+02:00">April
                                        2, 1941—9 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received April 3—6:16 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>448. Department’s 218, March 30. The substance of the Department’s
                                telegram under reference was given orally this morning to Prunas,
                                Chief of the American Section at the Foreign Office. He said that in
                                so far as he knew the Foreign Office had not yet received a full
                                report from the Italian Embassy in Washington on the matter and that
                                Ambassador Colonna had been instructed merely to inform the State
                                Department that Italy “reserved her rights” pending further
                                investigation. While he seemed unhappy and concerned because of the
                                action of the American authorities Prunas made no further
                                observations.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>